Title
API boundary truth, visibility cleanup, and public-surface finalization

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Make the codebase’s API and module boundaries truthful after the prior hardening sequence by removing fake or accidental public surfaces, tightening visibility, and aligning crate/module exposure with the actual supported product and research boundaries.

This packet is the finale of the CRUSHR-HARDEN-03 series.

It exists because, even after contracts, schemas, tool boundaries, and large-module decomposition are repaired, the codebase may still present a misleading public/internal boundary through stale `pub` surfaces, misleading module exposure, and docs/comments that imply support where none exists.

This is an API-truth packet.
It is not a feature packet.

