---------------------------------------------------------------------

Acceptance criteria

This packet is acceptable only if all of the following are true:

1. The codebase’s public/internal boundaries are materially more truthful.
2. Accidental public API exposure is reduced.
3. Stable product-facing surfaces remain intact and explicit.
4. Experimental/lab-only surfaces no longer masquerade as stable public API.
5. Docs/comments/README no longer imply unsupported API breadth.
6. The hardened codebase ends the series with a clear, defensible boundary story.
